    "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
    "body": "PowerShell is entirely based on .Net Core so before you continue with porting PowerShel you _should_ pass all tests in CoreCLR, CoreFX, CLI. After that I hope most problems (your questions above) will resolved automatically.\r\n\r\n>•Running any cmdlet gets me a not recognized as the name of a cmdlet, function... error.\r\n\r\nModules is not imported. There can be many reasons for this.\r\n\r\n> •Typing anything in results in repeated characters\r\n\r\nPerhaps it is a console problem. Try `TERM=xterm pwsh`. You could read [related issues](https://github.com/PowerShell/PowerShell/issues?utf8=%E2%9C%93&q=is%3Aissue+xTERM)",
